      <scopecontent id="aspace_f4e99015240749b43ef415e2aa005329">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Albert Cadwallader Worrell papers consist of correspondence, forestry research, unpublished manuscripts and records from Dr. Worrell's teaching activities abroad from 1951 to 1982.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_c618ad2ecfcdefdd908941dee66f8bc3">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Albert Cadwallader Worrell (1913-2000), Edwin W. Davis Professor Emeritus of Forest Policy, served on the faculty at Yale University from 1955 to 1983.  Dr. Worrell received his M.F. and PhD from the University and Michigan and taught at the University of Georgia from 1946 to 1955.  His many studies and writings in forest economics, and policy included efforts to value forests and environmental benefits.  During his years at Yale, he also held visiting appointments and universities in Chile, Germany, and Australia.</p>  
      </bioghist>
